> Pesto is one of those wonderful things that lends itself to infinite variation. The traditional way is great but there's no reason you can't mix things up occasionally. Mimi has come up with a fabulous Asian-inspired version that swaps basil and pine nuts for coriander and peanuts. It goes beautifully with crispy-skinned chicken atop stir-fried cabbage and noodles.

Preheat your oven to 200°C and put a large #saucepan{} of water on to boil for the noodles. Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Zest the @lime{1}. Put the @skin-on British chicken breasts{2} in a #mixing bowl{} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch} and the lime zest. Add a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} and massage in the seasoning.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat!

Lay the chicken in the frying pan, skin-side down (no oil), and cook until the skin is crispy, ~{5%minutes}. Turn and cook the flesh-side for ~{1%minute}. Meanwhile, add the @egg noodle nests{2} to the pan of boiling water. Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Drain in a #sieve{} then refill the pan with cold water and submerge the noodles. Set aside.

Once the chicken is crispy transfer it, skin-side up, to a #baking tray{}. Roast on the top shelf of your oven, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. When cooked, cover with foil and leave to one side. Don't wash your frying pan!

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @ginger{1}(peeled and grated) and @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @sweetheart cabbage{1/2} lengthways, remove the root and thinly slice widthways. Finely chop the @coriander{1}(finely chopped, stalks and all). Make a small hole in the @salted peanuts{40%g} bag and smash them into small pieces with a #rolling pin{}. Squeeze the lime juice into a small #bowl{} and mix in the coriander, peanuts, @soy sauce{25%ml} and @ketjap manis{25%ml}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in your now empty frying pan on medium heat. Add the ginger and garlic, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}. Then add the cabbage. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and some @black pepper{to taste}. Stir together and cook until softened, ~{5%minutes}. Drain the noodles in the sieve and add them to the pan. Stir together and cook until piping hot, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from the heat and add three-quarters of the dressing. Toss to coat.

Cut the chicken on the diagonal into thin slices. Serve the cabbage and noodles in #bowls{} with the chicken arranged on top. Finish with a drizzle of the remaining Asian pesto dressing. Enjoy!